s of authorship, authority, and book history. Kowalchuk’s revelatory interdisciplinary study offers unique insights into early modern women’s writings and the original sharing economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCooking, EnglishvEarly works to 1800. 0aEnglish literaturexWomen authors. 0aFormulas, recipes, etcvEarly works to 1800. 0aHome economicsvEarly works to 1800. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Books & Reading.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066594940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751010740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487510107423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487510107.jpg  a978-3-11-066594-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles